  "text": "Intriguingly, small G proteins, such as ras [CITATION_1] ) and rap2 [CITATION_2] ), are located in RE, which seems to be critical for their functions. Palmitoylation is quite important for ras and rap2 localization to RE, and a recent study reported that b 1 -AR is also palmitoylated [CITATION_3] ). RE is not only a simple receptacle for recycled molecules but also a dynamic organelle where many signaling molecules are localized. b 1 -AR may be modified or bound to signaling molecules through RE, resulting in other cellular functions.",
